<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-37-0473 </DOCNO><TEXT>Coal gasification seems to be a sound alternative for directly fired coalin power plants. The Dutch Board of Cooperating Electricity ProducersNV SEP seems to favor the option although it does not reject the nuclearoption. The environmentalists are in doubt: is coal gasification betterfor the environment and therefore, acceptable as energy technology oris it just another way to produce large quantities of pollutants. Thepetrochemical industry is in favor, NV SEP and the Dutch Government donot commit themselves, environmentalists are in doubt. 1 fig., 12 refs.</TEXT></DOC>